Parliament, Tuesday, 5 February 2019 – The Ad Hoc Committee to identify suitable candidates for the filling of vacancies at the Commission for Gender Equality (CGE) has cancelled its meeting that was to sit on Tuesday (5 February) to shortlist candidates. A later date will be communicated to reschedule the meeting. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE TO IDENTIFY SUITABLE CANDIDATES FOR THE FILLING OF VACANCIES AT THE COMMISSION FOR GENDER EQUALITY, MS NONHLANHLA NCUBE-NDABA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Yoliswa Landu
